    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>- Initial release based on version 22.1.3.
  * For details, see the release notes:
    - https://releases.llvm.org/22.1.0/docs/ReleaseNotes.html
    - https://releases.llvm.org/22.1.0/tools/clang/docs/ReleaseNotes.html
    - https://releases.llvm.org/22.1.0/tools/clang/tools/extra/docs/ReleaseNotes.html
    - https://releases.llvm.org/22.1.0/projects/libcxx/docs/ReleaseNotes.html
    - https://releases.llvm.org/22.1.0/tools/lld/docs/ReleaseNotes.html
  * New LLVM tools:
    - llvm-cas provides access to Content-addressable storage.
    - llvm-ir2vec generates embeddings for a given LLVM IR or MIR
      and supports triplet generation for vocabulary training and
      embedding generation.
    - clang-offload-packager is now called llvm-offload-binary.
    - llvm-offload-wrapper generates runtime registration code for
      a device binary image.
  * New LLDB tools:
    - lldb-mcp is an MCP server for LLDB.
    - yaml2macho-core can generate a macho-core from a YAML file.
- Rewrite all patches for monorepo layout.
- Add compiler-rt-lib-suffix.patch to fix compiler-rt build.
- Drop obsolete patches:
  * clang-fix-openmp-test.patch
  * compiler-rt-fix-relative-path.patch
  * llvm-projects-tools-order.patch
- Rebased patches:
  * bolt-link-shared-library.patch
  * check-no-llvm-exegesis.patch
  * clang-resourcedirs.patch
  * link-clang-shared.patch
  * llvm-fix-cov-test-i586.patch
  * lto-disable-cache.patch
- clang-riscv-triple.patch: Add riscv64-suse-linux to RISCV64Triples
- Drop ld.lld as an ld alternative (boo#1259813).
- Fix path in LLDB Python bindings for SLE/Leap 15.</comment>
    <requestid>1346272</requestid>
  </revision>
</revisionlist>
